  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "When initializing a hardhat project (with `hardhat` command), the initialization process forces one to use `npm` to install dependencies. This is less than ideal if I want to use anything but `npm` for package management. If I choose to not install dependencies, the `package.json` won't be updated at all.\r\n\r\nIt would be better if hardhat didn't run the install command, but rather left the installation up to the user. I, for example, would rather use `pnpm` so that all dependencies are installed only once on my system and were hard-linked to each project that uses hardhat and relevant dependencies.",
